oai_dc:dc.dc:title: David Lipscomb College Quartette, circa 1929 April
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A photograph of the David Lipscomb College Quartette, circa April, 1929. The second man pictured is Robert (Bob) Neil. The other persons in the varsity quartette are unidentified. Lipscomb University (20th century official name) was founded in Nashville, Tennessee in 1891 by David Lipscomb and James A. Harding. Forms part of the Nashville Room Historic Photographs Collection. 1 photograph : b & w ; 8 x 10 in.
